articles.author: Nicola Agius
articles.title: Google says all online content should be available for AI training unless publishers opt out - Search Engine Land
articles.description: The search engine has sent its proposal to the Australian government, urging policymakers to change existing copyright laws.
articles.content:
Google wants AI to be able to mine all digital content unless publishers opt out.
The search engine has put forward this proposal in a submission to the Australian government, calling on policymaker… [+2582 chars]
